Date: 0/0/1981
Source: Loughnan Glossary
Author: LOUGHNAN
Vol / Page: 59
Edition:
Quote: pakihi: as it also a Maori word for barren land, we have adopted the word to refer to a certain Westland-type soil that has been leached by constant heavy rain and is difficult to bring in to good pasture.
